Submission from: lal.cs.utah.edu (155.99.195.65)
Submitted by: peskin


Currently, if you run ATACS from a different directory from the directory with
the source file, and that source file includes another file without specifying
full path, atacs cannot find the included file.

For example:
194 song:~/atacs> pwd
/home/xia/peskin/atacs
195 song:~/atacs> ls -l `which atacs` examples/lapbN.csp examples/lapbsv.csp
-rwxr-xr-x   1 peskin   utmp     11453923 Jun 22 11:31
/home/xia/peskin/atacs/src/atacs*
-r--r--r--   1 peskin   utmp          706 Jun 22 12:17 examples/lapbN.csp
-r--r--r--   1 peskin   utmp          666 Jun 11 13:41 examples/lapbsv.csp
196 song:~/atacs> atacs -lc examples/lapbN
ATACS VERSION 4.1
Logging session in:  atacs.log
Compiling examples/lapbN.csp ... 
examples/lapbN.csp: line 1: cannot open 'lapbsv.csp'
examples/lapbN.csp: line 16: module 'lapb' not found
Storing process  to examples/.er
Storing process lapbN to examples/lapbN.er
ERROR:8:  No rules in system!

